               4. A praier for the Kingdome of God.
               
               
                  MErciful, and gratious God, which hast called vs 1. Thes. 2, verse. 12. vnto thy kingdome and glorie; and of thy fatherlie and good pleasure enioined vs this care, that first Mat. 6, 33. and afore al things we should seeke thy Kingdome, and the righteousnes thereof:
