               Inspire thy ministers, and preachers of thy word with thine holie Spirit, that they may vtter thy wil purelie as they haue receiued it from thine hands, retaining the forme of wholesome words 2. Timo. 1, verse. 13., and sounding onlie that doctrine which is vttered by thy Sonne out of thy bosome Iohn. 1, 18.. For otherwise, departing from the order of faith, and the rule of thy worde, they wil greatlie obscure the light of thy doctrine; and obtrude vpon vs the vanitie of their



owne inuentions. Wherefore let them speake thy word not deceiptfullie 2. Cor. 4, 2., but syncerelie, euen as from thee, and in thy sight.
