               For whatsoeuer is either in the heauens aboue, or in the earth beneath it is thine. Thine, O Lord, is the kingdome; thou art aboue al Princes &amp; Kings. Riches are thine, glorie is thine, and thou art Lorde



ouer al. In thee remaineth virtue, and power, greatnes, and gouernement.
