               Deck me with thy gifts &amp; goodnes. Wash me with water Eze. 36, 25, &amp; purge me with thy blood. Annoint me with thine oile of gladnes Psal. 45, 8. put vpon me thy roabes of righteousnes, and couer me with thy glorious purple; adorne me with the pretious stones of virtue, and place vpon mine head glorie and honor, that al mine ornament may be inward, and that I may please thee through hoping in thy mercie. For thou art mine husbande which louest me; my God whom I worship; and the head wherevnto I am subiect.
               
