                  O Christ the onelie mediator betweene God and man 1. Tim. 2, 5., which of thine ardent and vnspeakeable good wil6. tookest our flesh vpon thee, to become a sacrifice and raunsome for al mankinde: and for the better conceauing of that thy benefit didst ordaine before thy paineful passion, a perpetual memorie of thy loue, and that by erecting a couenant of the newe Testament Matth. 26, vers. 26, &amp;c. Mark. 14, 24 Luke. 22, vers. 19, &amp;c., which testifieth of thy presence, merite, power, and mercie, washing awaie dailie the sinnes of beleeuers:
